Hello,

Our team is currently working on adding autonomous paths to our code, using Advantage Kit. However, we’re running into an issue where the robot does not move when an auto routine is selected in simulation.

So far, we’ve observed two main issues:

  • The path does not flip when on the red alliance.
  • The path is being sent to execute but does not move the robot.

Here are some screenshots of what we’re seeing:

Auto is being ran, but the robot does not move:

image1919×1008 227 KB

Auto path not showing on PathPlanner and not commanding movement:

image1913×1002 69.3 KB

Our code can be found here: GitHub - PerkValleyRobotics/2025RobotCode at limelight

Has anyone encountered this issue before or have suggestions on how to debug this? Any help would be greatly appreciated!

Hello,

What we had found was that the wheel friction was set to zero so the robot was not able to move.

Just putting it here incase somebody made the same issue!
